<section id="jfaceeditor">
	<title>Tutorial: Editing the table content</title>
	<para>
		Create the following new classes
		in the new
		<code>de.vogella.jface.tableviewer.edit</code>
		package.
	</para>
	<para>
		<programlisting language="java">
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="../examples/editing/FirstNameEditingSupport.java" />
		</programlisting>
	</para>
	<para>
		<programlisting language="java">
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="../examples/editing/LastNameEditingSupport.java" />
		</programlisting>
	</para>
	<para>
		<programlisting language="java">
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="../examples/editing/GenderEditingSupport.java" />
		</programlisting>
	</para>
	<para>
		<programlisting language="java">
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="../examples/editing/MarriedEditingSupport.java" />
		</programlisting>
	</para>
	<para>
		Now assign <code>EditorSupport</code> objects to your <code>TableColumnViewers</code> in
		your
		<code>View</code> class. Replace the existing method <code>createColumns()</code> with the
		following one and adjust your imports.
	</para>
	<para>
		<programlisting language="java">
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="../examples/editing/View.java" />
		</programlisting>
	</para>
	<para>
		Run your application. You should now be able to modify the
		content of the JFace table.
	</para>
</section>